ZH: 别人的意见并不总是对的。
EN: Other people's opinions are not always correct.

ZH: 做人要学会尊重别人。
EN: To be a good person, one must learn to respect others.

ZH: 别人的成就不会嫉妒自己的进步。
EN: One should not envy their own progress due to others' accomplishments.

ZH: 他总是看着别人的眼色来做决定。
EN: He always makes decisions based on what other people think.

ZH: 在争论中，别人的观点可能会改变自己的立场。
EN: In a debate, other people's opinions may change one's stance.

ZH: 别人的喜好跟自己的可能不一样。
EN: Other people's preferences may not be the same as one's own.

ZH: 有时候，别人的建议比自己更有见地。
EN: Sometimes, other people's advice is more insightful than one's own.

ZH: 他总是为别人着想。
EN: He always thinks of others.

ZH: 别人的成功是可以学习和借鉴的。
EN: Other people's success can be learned from and emulated.

ZH: 在处理冲突时，要学会换位思考别人的感受。
EN: When handling conflicts, one should learn to consider other people's feelings.

ZH: 我们不能总是依赖别人做决定。
EN: We cannot always rely on others to make decisions.

ZH: 别人的错误并不表示自己可以不犯错。
EN: Other people's mistakes do not mean one cannot make mistakes.

ZH: 忙于帮助别人也不要忘记了照顾自己。
EN: While being busy helping others, one should not forget to take care of oneself.

ZH: 不要总是过度期望别人。
EN: Do not always have excessive expectations of others.

ZH: 自己做出的决定不要后悔，不要责怪别人。
EN: Do not regret the decisions one has made, and do not blame others.

ZH: 和别人交流时要尊重对方的观点。
EN: When communicating with others, one should respect their viewpoints.

ZH: 有时候别人的帮助会使事情变得更好。
EN: Sometimes, other people's help can make things better.

ZH: 别人的经验可以教会我们很多东西。
EN: Other people's experiences can teach us a lot.

ZH: 别和别人比较，要专注于自己的进步。
EN: Do not compare yourself with others, focus on your own progress.

ZH: 别人的批评也可以是一种成长的机会。
EN: Other people's criticisms can also be an opportunity for growth.
